- Mute channels/DMs (durable, cross-device; full silence) — v0.9.1.
- Suppress historical "deleted" tombstones; only live-session deletes tombstone — v0.9.2.
- Update-available banner via a WS hello{version} handshake — v0.9.3.
- Admin stats panel (user/channel/message counts + live connections) — v1.0.0.
- Autocomplete for @-pings (username + display name, channel-scoped, keyboard nav) — v1.0.4.
- Mobile swipe gestures (right = sidebar, left = members; horizontal vs. scroll disambiguated) — v1.0.5.
- Idle status (10-min timer, hidden-tab accelerated; ephemeral hub flag, amber dot same as away) — v1.0.6.
- Typing indicators (throttled WS frames, server-side 5 s TTL, channel-scoped relay, "X is typing…" above composer) — v1.0.7.
- Every message timestamp links to that point in history (window-around-id store
  query, #c<id>/m<id> hash, load+scroll+highlight, "viewing history" banner) —
  v1.0.8; v1.0.9 polish: canonical permalink hash helper (fixed a /m/ vs /m drift
  that broke shared links on fresh load) + feedback when an anchor is deleted/gone;
  v1.0.10: bidirectional history paging (after= cursor → scroll *down* loads newer)
  and the "viewing history" banner only shows when the window has a gap to the tail;
  v1.0.11: forward paging now holds scroll position instead of snapping to the
  bottom (the snap stranded mobile readers at the end so the next page never
  loaded), and prefetches ~a screen early so reading downward stays seamless;
  v1.0.12: scroll loading is now driven by IntersectionObserver sentinels (the
  scrollTop math never fired reliably on mobile), and a jump probes forward once
  so brief conversations fill the cut-off tail and never show a spurious banner.
- Message search (full-text, scoped to accessible channels) — v1.0.17. Postgres
  to_tsvector('english') + GIN functional index (migration 0007); websearch_to_tsquery
  tolerates arbitrary input. GET /api/search?q=&before=&limit= scopes to the caller's
  accessible channels (accessibleChannelIDs, same rule as canAccessChannel — DMs stay
  members-only even for mods), newest-first with keyset pagination. Header 🔍 opens a
  debounced search modal; clicking a hit reuses jumpToMessage. Renders via the
  escape-first formatMessage (no ts_headline, preserving the XSS invariant).
- Custom emojis (instance-wide :shortcode: images) — v1.0.19. emojis table
  (migration 0008) stores image bytes like avatars (BYTEA + mime, created_by SET
  NULL on user delete). GET /api/emojis (any member) + GET /api/emojis/{sc}/image;
  POST/DELETE are admin-only; create/delete broadcast emoji.add/emoji.delete to
  everyone so the registry updates live. format.js gained an optional emoji
  registry arg: it SPLITS each escaped segment on known :shortcode: tokens and
  renders <img class="emoji"> between text runs (same layering as code spans), so
  the markdown pass can never mangle the generated tag — preserving the
  escape-first XSS invariant even for underscore-bearing shortcodes. state.js
  holds the registry (setEmojis/upsertEmoji/removeEmoji); admin panel has an
  upload+manage section; the composer has a 😀 picker that inserts the token.
  v1.0.21: typing ":" opens inline autocomplete just like "@" — the mention
  popup was generalized into a two-kind completion controller (@ → user, : →
  shortcode) sharing one popup + keyboard nav; new pure colonQuery() mirrors
  atQuery() with the same boundary guard so URLs/times/ratios never false-trigger.
- Reactions (per-message emoji) — v1.0.22. message_reactions table (migration
  0009) PK (message_id, user_id, emoji) — one of each emoji per user per message
  is intrinsic and the add is idempotent (INSERT … ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING). emoji
  is EITHER a known custom :shortcode: OR a literal Unicode grapheme; the client
  resolves which at render (registry hit → <img>, else literal text).
  PUT/DELETE /api/messages/{id}/reactions carry the emoji in the body (no URL
  encoding of Unicode); any member with channel access may toggle their own, on a
  visible non-deleted message (deleted → 409, no access → 403). Validation is
  stdlib-only (no emoji lib, per the prime directive): a known shortcode, or
  validUnicodeEmoji — every rune a symbol/ZWJ/VS/keycap-base and ≥1 emoji-ish,
  admitting flags, skin-tone & ZWJ sequences and keycaps while rejecting words.
  One realtime event, reaction.update, carries the re-aggregated groups (not
  add/remove deltas — sidesteps client reconciliation); applyEvent folds it via
  setReactions. List/search/pins endpoints decorate messages in one batched query
  (ReactionsForMessages, no N+1); soft-delete sheds reactions (cascade covers hard
  delete). UI: pill row under each message (custom→img, else glyph; highlighted
  when you're a reactor; click toggles), a "react" action that floats the shared
  emoji picker (now carrying a common-Unicode palette alongside custom emoji), and
  read-only-but-toggleable pills in the pins modal (toggleReaction takes the
  pill's known "mine" so it's correct even when the pinned message is outside the
  loaded window). Search rows stay text-only — they're click-to-jump, so pills
  would fight the row click; reactions stay fully interactive in the live view.

